[ ] make the json schemas live, linked contracts not dead docs $ specifications/schemas/ describes the wire formats but the serde structs that define them live in the clearhead-core submodule — different repo, no enforced link, so they drift silently and only one schema is ever loaded at runtime (a single jsonld test). adding charter.id to the sidecar is the trigger: struct and schema must move in lockstep with nothing to catch a miss $ !2 +specifications,library #019f4f67-be9d-7f58-96f6-cc30b2f5741d
    >[ ] add a drift check that validates the serde structs against their schemas $ core cannot see specifications/, so this belongs in the platform integration CI over the pinned submodules — serialize a representative CharterMetadata and assert it validates, so struct-vs-schema drift fails a build instead of shipping $ +testing #019f4f67-be9d-70d6-b07a-d7f13098cef5
    >[ ] have emitted data files carry a \$schema pointer $ sidecars written with a \$schema key so editors validate on write and the file is self-describing — the declarative-filesystem theme, same spirit as recording charter.id in the sidecar $ +library #019f4f67-be9d-748c-986f-7739e16e4660
    >[ ] decide the schema source of truth and record it $ hand-maintained schema plus a drift test, or generate the schema from the structs (schemars) so drift is structurally impossible at the cost of coupling the format spec to the rust crate. decide in DECISIONS.md $ +specifications #019f4f67-be9d-7c7b-860d-bdd95659c486
